race.comment: MICHELANGELO (8) big drop in class first-up when a slashing nose winner over 1350m at Wyong. Held in high regard by the stable and will keep improving as he gets out in trip. Since fitted with a 1030m trial and should get the right tempo here. MONOPOLISTIC (9) Savabeel gelding who was heavily supported on debut when a slick winner over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Expected to have trained on and since ran eighth in a Rosehill trial over 1030m. Ready for this tougher contest from the good gate. BOTANIST (2) kept fresh at start three when taken to the front for a tenacious Maiden win over 1400m at Warwick Farm. Kept up to the mark with a 900m trial placing at Rosehill. Can push forward from the sticky gate and play a leading role. VALIANT BOMB (6) underrated gelding who comes here with a fitness edge fourth-up. Returned from a let-up with a plugging third over 1400m at Goulburn in Cl1 grade. Proven at the trip and not without each way claims.
